title: 3 charts show China is far from meeting its 'phase one' trade commitment to the U.S.
text: China has so far bought less than a quarter of the targeted full-year amount of U.S. goods agreed under the deal, according to Peterson Institute for International Economics.

title: Gold Prices Rebound After Rout
text: Gold’s rollercoaster ride continues in 2020, rebounding back above $1,900 in what has been a wild week that’s seen the precious metal hit a record high before plunging below that key level. Still, it remains one of the best performing commodities of 2020. Bloomberg’s Krystal Chia reports on “Bloomberg Daybreak: Asia.”

title: U.S. July deficit falls to $63 billion on delayed tax payments

title: Trump's executive order only guarantees $300 per week in enhanced unemployment for some workers

text: The gap between the parties on coronavirus stimulus is a "chasm," Nancy Pelosi said as it is unclear when relief talks will restart.
